<subSubSection id="C337088DF76EB12FB182FC2C316A4670" pageId="27" pageNumber="548" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B925B06F76EB12FB182FC2C316A4670" blockId="27.[151,1437,619,1330]" pageId="27" pageNumber="548">
COMMENTS: The only entry in Wahlberg’s journal for this day (
<date id="FF937DC6F76EB12FB2CFFC2C365F40AF" box="[906,1126,979,1005]" pageId="27" pageNumber="548" value="1841-11-18">18 November 1841</date>
) is “fully occupied”. However, he recorded collecting a specimen of “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F76EB12FB3D4FC0831BF4753" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1766" box="[657,902,1015,1041]" class="Aves" family="Hirundinidae" genus="Hirundo" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="548" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="senegalensis">
<emphasis id="B9598714F76EB12FB3D4FC0831BF4753" box="[657,902,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="548">Hirundo senegalensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” [in error for 
<taxonomicName id="4C2D2085F76EB12FB569FC08374F4753" authorityName="Sundevall" authorityYear="1850" box="[1068,1398,1015,1041]" class="Aves" family="Hirundinidae" genus="Hirundo" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="27" pageNumber="548" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="semirufa" subGenus="Cecropis">
<emphasis id="B9598714F76EB12FB569FC0836B24753" box="[1068,1163,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="548">Hirundo</emphasis>
(
<emphasis id="B9598714F76EB12FB5D8FC0837384753" box="[1181,1281,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="548">Cecropis</emphasis>
) 
<emphasis id="B9598714F76EB12FB451FC08374F4753" box="[1300,1398,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="548">semirufa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] at Mooi River (Potchefstroom) on 8 November and then another specimen on 14 November on the southern edge of the Magaliesberg, close to Hartebeespoort. The Potchefstroom specimen has not been located in the collections. The restricted 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F76EB12FB04DFB9C3301473F" box="[264,312,1123,1149]" pageId="27" pageNumber="548">type</typeStatus>
locality suggested by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFBC26F7F76EB12FB37EFB9C311D473F" author="Gyldenstolpe, N." box="[571,804,1123,1149]" pageId="27" pageNumber="548" pagination="264 - 292" refId="ref28785" refString="Gyldenstolpe, N. (1934) The travels and collections of Johan August Wahlberg, 1810 - 1856: a pioneer naturalist in South Africa. Ibis, 76, 264 - 292. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1474 - 919 X. 1934. tb 01567. x" type="journal article" year="1934">Gyldenstolpe (1934)</bibRefCitation>
is unlikely. The confluence between the Crocodile and Hennops Rivers is well south of the track that Wahlberg was thought to have used when travelling from Holfontein to Hartebeesport (map B, p. 
<quantity id="4CD5F6E3F76EB12FB0A7FB5430154787" box="[482,556,1195,1221]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2766" pageId="27" pageNumber="548" unit="in" value="129.0">129 in</quantity>
Craig &amp; Hummel 1992). If the 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F76EB12FB2E4FB5431E84787" box="[929,977,1195,1221]" pageId="27" pageNumber="548">type</typeStatus>
was collected on 18 November, the TL should be restricted to Hartebeespoort. If the 
<typeStatus id="5496E5A4F76EB12FB3DFFB3030F347AB" box="[666,714,1231,1257]" pageId="27" pageNumber="548">type</typeStatus>
was collected on 
<date id="FF937DC6F76EB12FB2DDFB30364D47AB" box="[920,1140,1231,1257]" pageId="27" pageNumber="548" value="1841-11-14">14 November 1841</date>
, Wahlberg was camped at “Herman Potgieter’s farm” at Olifantsnek on this day and reached Hartebeespoort on the 15 November (see “Problems with labels and collecting localities” in the Introduction).
</paragraph>
